00:00:07,888 --> 00:00:11,172
July 4, 1963

4
00:00:11,968 --> 00:00:14,315
Those marched in 
the streets were just kids.

5
00:00:14,315 --> 00:00:17,711
And the police were using 
fire hoses and dogs on 'em.

6
00:00:17,711 --> 00:00:19,443
Fillin' their jails with children.

7
00:00:19,443 --> 00:00:21,763
I'm just thankful we left Biloxi.

8
00:00:21,763 --> 00:00:23,514
I think Dr. King's right.

9
00:00:23,514 --> 00:00:25,329
That march on 
Washington next month?

10
00:00:25,329 --> 00:00:26,951
That'll change people's minds.

11
00:00:26,951 --> 00:00:29,313
Marching the streets? 
Isn't the asnwer, son.

12
00:00:29,313 --> 00:00:30,662
What is Pops?

13
00:00:30,662 --> 00:00:34,167
Dignity, hard work, education.

14
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:35,956
Things in life that matter most.

15
00:00:35,956 --> 00:00:38,095
Dr. King says, 
our lives begin to end

16
00:00:38,095 --> 00:00:40,664
the day we become silent 
about the things that matter.

17
00:00:40,664 --> 00:00:43,390
- Your son's gotta point, Donald.
- Oh, my son?

18
00:00:44,838 --> 00:00:47,598
- Where you think he get all his sass from?
- From your mother side.

19
00:00:47,598 --> 00:00:49,915
But that's a whole other story.

20
00:00:58,710 --> 00:01:00,483
Donald Williams.

21
00:01:00,483 --> 00:01:01,946
I'm Billy Jones.

22
00:01:01,946 --> 00:01:03,593
From TBL defense systems?

23
00:01:03,810 --> 00:01:06,580
- Glad to finally meet you, Billy.
- You're all moved in then, I suppose?

24
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:08,187
Looking forward to 
seeing the plant tomorrow.

25
00:01:08,187 --> 00:01:10,662
- Why don't I take that from you?
- Thank you.

26
00:01:13,759 --> 00:01:15,687
I'm Judith.
Billy's sister-in-law.

27
00:01:15,687 --> 00:01:18,530
- So, pleased to meet you.
- Oh, Mary Williams, likewise.

28
00:01:18,530 --> 00:01:21,510
This is my husband 
Donald, and our son Ezekiel.

29
00:01:21,510 --> 00:01:23,729
You can call me 
Zeke for short, ma'am.

30
00:01:23,729 --> 00:01:25,184
Zeke, it is then.

31
00:01:25,184 --> 00:01:27,918
My husband Henry is 
around here, somewhere...

32
00:01:27,918 --> 00:01:29,804
Sweetheart!

33
00:01:31,641 --> 00:01:33,789
I understand you're 
in military, Mr. Willams?

34
00:01:33,789 --> 00:01:35,594
Did they train you 
to work on planes?

35
00:01:35,594 --> 00:01:37,208
Well, actually I'm an engineer.

36
00:01:37,208 --> 00:01:38,531
I build'em.

37
00:01:38,531 --> 00:01:41,402
Mr. Williams will be 
overseeing operations in TBL.

38
00:01:41,402 --> 00:01:42,752
He's your boss, Billy?

39
00:01:42,752 --> 00:01:47,504
Henry, the Williams are our new neighbors 
they just came up from Mississippi.

40
00:01:47,625 --> 00:01:48,922
Welcome.

41
00:01:48,922 --> 00:01:50,653
I better help Charlotte
get some dessert.

42
00:01:50,653 --> 00:01:53,692
Jump in there, Zeke.
Before my neice gobbles it all down.

43
00:01:54,133 --> 00:01:55,858
Jell-O!

44
00:01:55,858 --> 00:01:57,429
I thought you 
wanted cake, Charlotte.

45
00:01:57,429 --> 00:01:58,888
I don't like cake, Daddy.

46
00:01:58,888 --> 00:02:00,206
Sure you do.

47
00:02:00,206 --> 00:02:01,656
You love cake.

48
00:02:16,295 --> 00:02:18,103
With this faith we will 
be able to work together,

49
00:02:18,103 --> 00:02:20,514
to pray together, 
to struggle together,

50
00:02:20,514 --> 00:02:24,250
to go to jail together, 
to stand up for freedom together...

51
00:02:44,885 --> 00:02:46,466
Holy moly!

52
00:02:46,466 --> 00:02:49,106
- What is that?
- Let's get out of here.

53
00:02:49,820 --> 00:02:52,142
It's a kid.

54
00:02:53,889 --> 00:02:55,623
Don't touch it, Willy!

55
00:02:55,623 --> 00:02:58,270
The fuzz will put you in the slammer.

56
